duismtoday.com/modules/smartsection/item.php?itemid=4798|title=Hinduism Today Magazine|last=Academy|first=Himalayan|website=www.hinduismtoday.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-31}}</ref>, ''[[The Making of the Mahatma]]''. Other notable roles are as the protagonist Unni in the [[Malayalam]] film ''[[Agnisakshi (1999 film)|Agnisakshi]]'', and the fictional detective [[Byomkesh Bakshi]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kapur|first1=Rajit|title=Even now people call Rajit Kapur Byomkesh Bakshi|url=http://www.gqindia.com/get-smart/pop-culture/even-now-people-call-rajit-kapur-byomkesh-bakshi-gq-india/|website=GQ India|publisher=GQ|accessdate=6 January 2016}}</ref> {{Third-party inline|date=January 2016}} in the eponymous ''[[Byomkesh Bakshi (1993 TV series)|television series]]'', directed by [[Basu Chatterjee]] and broadcast on [[Doordarshan]]. His debut film was ''[[Suraj Ka Satvan Ghoda]]'' (1992), directed by [[Shyam Benegal]].\n\n==Career==\n\nRajit Kapur played the role of the famous [[Bengalis|Bengali]] detective [[Byomkesh Bakshi]] in the eponymously named TV series, ''[[Byomkesh Bakshi (1993 TV series)|Byomkesh Bakshi]]'' (1993). Byomkesh Bakshi is a fictitious character created by the popular Bengali writer [[Sharadindu Bandyopadhyay]]. [[Basu Chatterjee]] directed a TV show based on the stories of Bandyopadhyay, and Rajit Kapur played the lead role. The show was very popular and Rajit Kapur achieved his first media recognition through this show. Kapoor is also a very prominent theatre actor and director in india. He has also acted in several hit movies recently like [[Kick (2014 film)| Kick]] , [[Uri: The Surgical Strike]] and [[Raazi]]\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n! Year\n!  Title !! Role !! Director !! Notes\n|-\n| 2019\n|''[[Bypass Road (film)|Bypass Road]]''|| Pratap || Naman Nitin Mukesh ||<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/movies-to-look-forward-to/bypass-road-neil-nitin-mukesh-is-all-praise-for-senior-actor-rajit-kapur/photostory/69514673.cms|title=\u2018Bypass Road\u2019: Neil Nitin Mukesh is all praise for senior actor Rajit Kapur}}</ref>\n|-\n| TBD\n|''[[Life's Good (film)|Life's Good]] ''|| TBA || [[Anant Mahadevan]] ||\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[22 Yards]]''\n|\n|Mitali Ghoshal \n|\n|-\n| 2019\n|''[[Uri: The Surgical Strike]]''||Prime Minister of India||[[Aditya Dhar]] ||  \n|-\n| 2018\n|''[[Raazi]]''|| Hidayat Khan || [[Meghna Gulzar]] ||  \n|-\n| 2018\n|''[[Phir Se...]]''|| Krish || [[Kunal Kohli]]<br>Ajay Bhuyan ||\n|-\n| 2017\n|''[[A Gentleman]]''|| Kavya's father || [[Raj Nidimoru and Krishna D.K.]] || \n|-\n| 2017\n|''[[The Wishing Tree (2017 film)|The Wishing Tree]]''|| Fatima's Father || Manika Sharma || \n|-\n| 2017\n|''[[Begum Jaan]]''|| Ilias Khan ||  Srijit Mukherji ||\n|-\n| 2016\n|''[[Anna (2016 film)|Anna: Kisan Baburao Hazare]]''||  || Shashank Udapurkara ||\n|-\n| 2016\n|''[[Baar Baar Dekho]]''|| Panditji || [[Nitya Mehra]] || Special appearance\n|-\n| 2016\n|''[[Ki & Ka]]''|| Mr. Kumar Bansal || [[R. Balki]] || \n|-\n| 2015\n|''[[Uvaa]]''|| Principal || Jasbir Bhaati ||\n|-\n| 2015\n|''[[Roy (film)|Roy]]''|| Detective Wadia || Vikramjit Singh ||\n|-\n| 2014\n|''[[Dishkiyaoon]]''|| Viki's Dad || Sanamjit Singhalwar ||\n|-\n| 2014\n|''[[Kick (2014 film)|Kick]]''|| Dr. Jayant Verma || [[Sajid Nadiadwala]] ||\n|-\n| 2013\n|''[[Singh Saab the Great]]''|| Iqbal || [[Anil Sharma]] ||\n|-\n| 2013\n|''[[Mishawr Rawhoshyo]]''|| Al Mamun || [[Srijit Mukherji]] || Bengali film\n|-\n| 2011\n|''[[Shaitan (film)|Shaitan]]''|| Amy's Father || [[Bejoy Nambiar]] ||\n|-\n| 2011\n|''[[Dam 999]]''|| Shankaran || Sohan roy ||  UAE\u2013Indian co-production film\n|-\n| 2011\n|''[[Monica (film)|Monica]]''|| Raj Jaitley ||  Sushen Bhatnagar ||\n|-\n| 2010\n|''[[Guzaarish (2010 film)|Guzaarish]]''|| Public Prosecutor, Vipin Patel || [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]] ||\n|-\n| 2010\n|''[[Well Done Abba]]''|| Inspector Rishab Reddy || [[Shyam Benegal]] || \