hastri || \n|- \n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''[[Star Bestsellers|Star Bestsellers (Episode unknown-'Tripti')]]''\n|| 1999||{{yes}} ||{{yes}} || ||Also, writer and producer  \n|- \n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''[[Star Bestsellers|Star Bestsellers (Episode 12-'Prayas')]]''\n|| 1999||{{yes}} || || ||  \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''[[Star Bestsellers|Star Bestsellers (Episode 8-'Shuruaat')]]''\n|| 1999||{{yes}} ||{{yes}} || ||Also, producer  \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''Junoon''\n|| 1997-98||{{yes}} || || ||  \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''[[Byomkesh Bakshi (TV Series)|Byomkesh Bakshi]]'' (Season 2)\n|| 1997||{{yes}} || || Byomkesh Bakshi || \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''Yugantar''\n|| 1995-96||{{yes}} || || ||\n|-   \n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''[[Byomkesh Bakshi (TV Series)|Byomkesh Bakshi]]'' (Season 1)\n|| 1993||{{yes}} || ||[[Byomkesh Bakshi]] || \n|-   \n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''[[Kshitij Ye Nahi]]''\n|| 1991||{{yes}} || || || \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" align=\"left\" |''Ghar Jamai''\n|| 1986||{{yes}} || || ||  \n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n*'''1996:''' [[National Film Award for Best Actor]] - ''[[The Making of the Mahatma]]''\n*'''1998:''' [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actor]] - ''[[Agnisakshi (1999 film)|Agnisakshi]]''\n*'''2010:''' Imagine India Film Festival, Spain, Award for Best Actor - ''[[Do Paise Ki Dhoop, Chaar Aane Ki Baarish]]''<ref>http://www.imagineindia.net/eng/News/News.php?id=3823499669042862790</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\nhttps://www.youthkiawaaz.com/2015/01/rajit-kapur-interview/\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0438496|name=Rajit Kapur}}\n\n{{NationalFilmAwardBestActor}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kapur, Rajit}}\n[[Category:Indian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Best Actor National Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n", "name_user": "GreaterPonce665", "label": "safe", "comment": "gq 'is' a Third-party source", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rajit_Kapur"}
{"title_page": "Shawn Grate", "text_new": "{{short description|American serial killer on death row}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox criminal\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name = Shawn Grate\n| honorific_suffix = \n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image =  Shawn Michael Grate.png\n| image_upright = \n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = Ashland County Sheriff's Office mugshot\n| birth_name = Shawn Michael Grate\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|08|08|mf=yes}}\n| birth_place = \n| disappeared_date = \n| disappeared_place = \n| disappeared_status = \n| death_date =     <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place = \n| death_cause = \n| body_discovered = \n| resting_place = \n| resting_place_coordinates =\n| monuments = \n| residence = \n| nationality = [[American (ethnicity)|American]]\n| other_names = \n| ethnicity = \n| citizenship = \n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| occupation = \n| years_active = \n| employer = \n| organization = \n| agent = \n| known_for = Convicted serial killings 2006, 2015\u20132016\n| notable_works = \n| style = \n| home_town = [[Marion, Ohio]]<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/local/2016/10/01/shawn-grate-cold-blooded-charmer-life-story-accused-serial-killer-ashland-mansfield-marion-ohio/91340968/|title= Shawn Grate: A cold-blooded charmer|author=|date= October 1, 2016|work= Mansfield News Journal|publisher=|accessdate= November 30, 2017}}</ref>\n| salary = \n| net_worth = \n| height = \n| weight = \n| television = \n| title = \n| term = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| party = \n| movement = \n| opponents = \n| boards = \n| religion = \n| denomination = \n| criminal_charge = \n| conviction_penalty = [[Capital punishment|Death penalty]] (June 1, 2018)<br />Life without parole (March 1 and September 11, 2019)\n| conviction_status = Awaiting execution at the [[Chillicothe Correctional Institution]]\n| spouse = Amber Grate (2011-2012)<ref>https://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/real-life/news-life/the-wife-of-serial-killer-shawn-grate-speaks-out-about-marriage/news-story/ce1553c1283cc0b61dc93008b54a98a4</ref>\n| children = 3\n| parents =        \n| relatives = \n| callsign = \n| awards = \n| website = \n| allegiance =\n| motive = \n| conviction = Murder (2 counts) (May 7, 2018)<br />Murder (2 counts) (March 1, 2019)<br />Murder (1 count) (September 11, 2019)\n| reward_amount = \n| capture_status = \n| wanted_by = \n| partners = \n| wanted_since = \n| time_at_large = \n| escaped = \n| escape_end = \n| comments = \n| victims = 5 known (one known as \"Jane Doe\" who was kidnapped and raped multiple times was able to escape); Multiple bodies found, believed to be victims of Grate.\n| date = \n| time = \n| beginyear = 2006\n| endyear = 2016\n| country = United States\n| states = [[Ohio]]\n| locations = [[Ashland County, Ohio|Ashland County]], [[Marion County, Ohio|Marion County]], [[Richland County, Ohio|Richland County]]\n| targets = \n| fatalities = \n| injuries = \n| weapons = \n| apprehended = September 13, 2016\n| imprisoned = \n| module =\n| signature =\n| signature_size =\n| signature_alt = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Shawn Michael Grate''' (born August 8, 1976<ref name=WMFD_69898>{{cite news|last1=Jackman|first1=Jay|title=23 Felony Count Indictments Against Convicted Serial Killer|url=http://www.northcentralohio.com/news/single.asp?story=69898|accessdate=September 23, 2016|work=WMFD|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026233125/http://www.northcentralohio.com/news/single.asp?story=69898|archive-date=October 26, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>) is an [[Demography of the United States|American]] convicted [[serial killer]] who was convicted on two counts of [[Aggravation (law)|aggravated]] [[murder]] on May 7, 2018, in [[Ashland County, Ohio|Ashland County]], [[Ohio]], pleaded guilty to two additional murders on March 1, 2019 in [[Richland County, Ohio]], and who pleaded guilty to an additional murder on September 11, 2019 in [[Marion County, Ohio]].\n\n==Biography==\nGrate graduated from [[River Valley High School (Caledonia, Ohio)|River Valley High School]] in 1995.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.richlandsource.com/news/grate-s-ex-wife-releases-statement/article_7ebfacc8-7b57-11e6-ab9d-63cfe72c082d.html\n |title=Grate's ex-wife releases statement\n |last=Carr\n |first=Dillon\n |date=September 15, 2016\n |website=Richland Source\n |publisher=\n |access-date=November 30, 2017\n |quote= }}</ref>\n\nA [[grand jury]] [[indict]]ed Grate on two counts of [[Aggravation (law)|aggravated]] [[murder]] in the deaths of two women, Stacey Stanley and Elizabeth Griffith, and the [[kidnapping]] and multiple [[Rape|sexual assaults]] of an unidentified woman whose [[9-1-1|911]] call to [[Ashland, Ohio|Ashland]] police led to Grate's arrest on September 13, 2016.  In court documents her name has been [[Redaction|redacted]]. She is being referred to as \"Jane Doe\". Grate was indicted on 23 counts, all first, second, or third-degree [[Felony|felonies]]; lesser charges include [[breaking and entering]], [[burglary]], and [[tampering with evidence]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tunnell|first1=Christopher|title=PDF Released: Grate Indictment 22 Sept 16|url=https://twitter.com/AshlandCoPros/status/779036910719229952|website=Twitter|accessdate=September 23, 2016}}</ref>  \n\nHe was represented in court by [[Public defender|court-appointed attorney]] Rolf Whitney,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sams|first1=Dylan|title=Grate pleads not guilty to two counts of murder, one count kidnapping|url=http://www.times-gazette.com/local%20news/2016/09/19/grate-pleads-not-guilty-to-two-counts-of-murder-one-count-kidnapping|accessdate=September 26, 2016|work=Ashland Times-Gazette}}</ref> who entered a plea of not guilty on all charges on behalf of Grate.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dunning|first1=Shanice|title=Suspected serial killer Shawn Grate pleads not guilty|url=http://www.cleveland19.com/story/33276947/suspected-serial-killer-shawn-grate-to-be-arraigned-thurs|accessdate=October 10, 2016|work=Cleveland 19 News}}</ref> In a press interview Grate confessed to five murders.<ref name=QAndACleveland19>{{cite news|last1=Nist|first1=Cassie|title=Q&A from jail: Shawn Grate says his victims didn't want to live|url=http://www.cleveland19.com/story/33343964/suspected-serial-killer-shawn-grate-grants-interview-from-ashland-county-jail|accessdate=October 10, 2016|work=Cleveland 19 News}}</ref> Grate's attorneys later filed a plea of not guilty by reason of insanity.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Steer|first1=Jen|title=Accused Ashland serial killer pleads insanity|url=http://fox8.com/2016/12/28/accused-ashland-serial-killer-pleads-insanity/|accessdate=January 4, 2017|work=WJW Fox 8 Cleveland|date=December 28, 2016}}</ref> His trial date was set for November 6, 2017,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mills|first1=Emily|title=Shawn Grate's trial date set for next November|url=http://www.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/2016/10/31/shawn-grates-trial-date-set-next-november/93086374/|accessdate=November 7, 2016|work=Mansfield News Journal|date=October 31, 2016}}</ref> and was later delayed to April 9, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Busbey|first1=Tim|title=Accused Ashland serial killer Shawn Grate's trial delayed until April 9|url=http://www.richlandsource.com/ashland_source/accused-ashland-serial-killer-shawn-grate-s-trial-delayed-until/article_3dda90c4-8c31-11e7-81ea-7b54d0d5f78e.html|accessdate=August 29, 2017|work=Richland Source|date=August 28, 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sams|first1=Dylan|title=Trial for Shawn Grate rescheduled for April 2018|url=https://www.times-gazette.com/local%20news/2017/08/28/trial-for-shawn-grate-rescheduled-for-april-2018|accessdate=August 29, 2017|work=Ashland Times-Gazette|date=August 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Trial of accused serial killer Shawn Grate delayed until next year|url=http://www.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/2017/08/28/trial-accused-serial-killer-grate-delayed/607622001/|accessdate=August 29, 2017|work=Mansfield News Journal|date=August 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAshland County [[prosecutor]] Christopher R. Tunnell said that given the \"...depraved actions and the gruesome evidence\", he would seek the [[death penalty]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Ashland prosecutor seeks death penalty against suspected serial killer|url=http://nbc4i.com/2016/09/22/ashland-prosecutor-seeks-death-penalty-against-suspected-serial-killer/|accessdate=September 26, 2016|work=WCMH-TV NBC4}}</ref>\n\nShawn Grate has also been charged in the deaths of his former girlfriend Candice Cunningham and Rebekah Leicy in neighboring Richland County,<ref>{{cite news|title=Convicted murderer Shawn Grate pleads not guilty to Richland County charges|url=https://eu.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/2018/09/13/convicted-murderer-shawn-grate-pleads-not-guilty-richland-charges/1291554002/|accessdate=September 14, 2018|work=Mansfield News Journal|date=September 13, 2018}}</ref> and has also been charged in the death of Dana Nicole Lowrey, 23, who died in 2006 and was found in 2007 in Marion County.<ref name=NBC4_9_20_16>{{cite news|title=Ashland killer connection reopens 2015 case|url=http://nbc4i.com/2016/09/20/ashland-killer-connection-reopens-2015-case/|accessdate=September 26, 2016|work=WCMH-TV NBC4}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Serial killer Shawn Grate charged in Marion County in woman's 2006 death  |url=https://eu.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/crime/2019/06/06/serial-killer-shawn-grate-charged-marion-county-womans-2007-death/1365551001/|accessdate=June 6, 2019|work=Mansfield News Journal|date=June 6, 2019}}</ref>  In the second of two letters he sent to [[Cleveland]] news station [[WEWS-TV|WEWS]] (News 5 Cleveland) reporter Megan Hickey, Grate attributed his motives to \"[[Welfare|government assistance]]\", writing that it took his victims' minds.  \"They were already dead, just their bodies were flopping wherever it can flop but their minds were already dead! The state took their minds. Once they started receiving their monthly checks\".  Grate claimed he once received a $197 [[Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program|food card]] and that he \"never was able to receive any encouragement, though many bodies received 700\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hickey|first1=Megan|title=Suspected serial killer Shawn Grate reveals \"why\" he murdered victims in letters to News 5|url=http://www.newsnet5.com/news/local-news/suspected-serial-killer-shawn-grate-reveals-why-he-murdered-victims-in-letters-to-news-5|accessdate=October 6, 2016|work=WEWS News 5 Cleveland}}</ref>\n\nAfter Grate gave details of the murders to two different news organizations while in custody, attorneys for the defense and prosecution jointly requested and obtained a [[gag order]] preventing Grate from communicating any further with the media.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Barbash|first1=Fred|title=The twisted confessions of Shawn Grate, who says he killed 5 women|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/10/14/the-twisted-confessions-of-shawn-grate-who-says-he-killed-5-women/|accessdate=October 24, 2016|work=The Washington Post}}</ref> On January 6, 2017, a competency hearing determined Grate is fit to stand trial.<ref>{{cite news|title=Grate competent to stand trial|url=http://www.times-gazette.com/local%20news/2017/01/06/grate-competent-to-stand-trial|accessdate=January 10, 2017|work=Ashland Times-Gazette|date=January 6, 2017}}</ref> An evaluation released March 6, based on a January 17 assessment to evaluate Grate's claim of insanity, declared that he was not insane at the time the crimes were committed.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Caudill|first1=Mark|title=Grate ruled competent to stand trial|url=http://www.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/local/2017/01/06/grate-ruled-competent-stand-trial/96238260/|accessdate=January 10, 2017|work=Mansfield News Journal|date=January 6, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Caudil|first1=Mark|title=Evaluation: Shawn Grate not insane at time of killings|url=http://www.wkyc.com/news/local/ohio/evaluation-shawn-grate-not-insane-at-time-of-killings/420130608|accessdate=March 20, 2017|work=WKYC|date=March 6, 2017}}</ref> Grate's counsel then withdrew the plea of not guilty by reason of insanity on April 7, 2017.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Busbey|first1=Tim|title=Shawn Grate's attorneys withdraw insanity plea|url=http://www.richlandsource.com/ashland_source/shawn-grate-s-attorneys-withdraw-insanity-plea/article_a3fd8f4c-1bab-11e7-96da-53a4563772d1.html|accessdate=April 19, 2017|work=Richland Source|date=April 7, 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>https://www.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/2020/02/04/mansfield-house-where-serial-killer-shawn-grate-stayed-demolished/4654001002/</ref>\n\n[[File:House at 363 Covert Court, Ashland, OH.jpg|thumb|363 Covert Court in Ashland, OH where Grate was arrested, a public memorial is in front of the house. The house has since been demolished.]]\nIn a settlement with the owner, the City of Ashland obtained ownership of the house where Grate was apprehended, two bodies were discovered, and a kidnapped woman was rescued by police. The city is pursuing a federal grant with the intention of demolishing the house.<ref name=\"Ashland Times-Gazette\">{{cite news|last1=Sams|first1=Dylan|title=Pump House to sign properties over to city in foreclosure case|url=http://www.times-gazette.com/news/20170912/pump-house-to-sign-properties-over-to-city-in-foreclosure-case|accessdate=September 13, 2017|work=Ashland Times-Gazette|date=September 12, 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sams|first1=Dylan|title=Ashland wants to demolish the houses where Shawn Grate was found last year|url=https://www.times-gazette.com/local%20news/2017/07/14/ashland-wants-to-demolish-the-houses-where-shawn-grate-was-found-last-year|accessdate=July 17, 2017|agency=Ashland Times-Gazette|date=July 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\u201cThere is a settlement agreement among the parties that essentially obligates the Pump House to transfer all property that is the subject of this action to the city of Ashland and transfer their title thereto, provided that the city pays off the sums owed to the county for delinquent taxes and to the Muskingum Watershed District,\u201d said Andrew Bush, assistant law director for the city of Ashland.<ref name=\"Ashland Times-Gazette\"/>\n\n== Trials ==\nGrate's trial for the Ashland crimes began with two weeks of jury selection on April 9, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|last1=McNaull|first1=Courtney|title=Jury selection begins in Shawn Grate case|url=http://www.richlandsource.com/ashland_source/jury-selection-begins-in-shawn-grate-case/article_4a052884-3bed-11e8-9772-f7342d9a5bf9.html|accessdate=April 9, 2018|work=Richland Source|date=April 9, 2018|language=en}}</ref> The trial began with opening statements on April 23.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sams|first1=Dylan|title=Prosecutor: Shawn Grate case \u201cnot a whodunnit\u201d|url=http://www.times-gazette.com/news/20180423/shawn-grate-not-whodunnit-case-prosecutor-says|accessdate=April 23, 2018|work=Ashland Times-Gazette|date=April 23, 2018|language=en}}</ref> On May 2, Grate pleaded guilty to 15 of the charges against him.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sams|first1=Dylan|title=Accused killer Grate pleads guilty to 15 non-murder charges|url=http://www.times-gazette.com/news/20180502/accused-killer-grate-pleads-guilty-to-15-non-murder-charges|accessdate=May 3, 2018|agency=Ashland Times-Gazette|date=May 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Accused Ashland serial killer Shawn Grate pleads guilty to several charges|url=http://fox8.com/2018/05/02/accused-ashland-serial-killer-shawn-grate-pleading-guilty-to-several-charges/|accessdate=May 3, 2018|work=WJW Fox 8 Cleveland|date=May 2, 2018}}</ref> On May 7, Grate was found guilty of murdering Stacey Stanley and Elizabeth Griffith.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jury finds Shawn Grate guilty of murder, sexual assault in Ohio|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/ohio-serial-killer-case-sent-jury-death-two-women-n872001|accessdate=May 8, 2018|work=NBC NEWS|date=May 7, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Accused serial killer Shawn Grate found guilty of aggravated murder, kidnapping|url=http://fox8.com/2018/05/07/closing-arguments-set-for-today-in-trial-of-accused-serial-killer/|accessdate=May 8, 2018|work=WJW Fox 8 Cleveland|date=May 7, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Sams|first1=Dylan|title=GRATE TRIAL: Guilty on all 8 counts|url=http://www.times-gazette.com/news/20180507/grate-trial-guilty-on-all-8-counts|accessdate=May 8, 2018|work=Ashland Times-Gazette|date=May 7, 2018|language=en}}</ref> On June 1, Grate was sentenced to death.<ref name=\"News Journal Death Sentence\">{{cite news|title=Crowd in court applauds death sentence for Shawn Grate|url=https://eu.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/2018/06/01/shawn-grate-sentenced-death-2016-murders/645107002/|accessdate=June 1, 2018|work=Mansfield News Journal|date=June 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Sams |first1=Dylan |title=Judge sentences Grate to death, families mourn |url=http://www.times-gazette.com/news/20180601/judge-sentences-grate-to-death-in-two-murders |accessdate=June 1, 2018 |work=Ashland Times-Gazette |date=June 1, 2018 |language=en}}</ref> An initial execution date was set upon conviction for [[List of offenders executed in the United States in 2018|September 13, 2018]],<ref name=\"News Journal Death Sentence\"/> however the execution was stayed due to a pending appeal to the Ohio Supreme Court.<ref name=SourceSept18>{{cite news |last1=McNaull |first1=Courtney |title=Serial killer Shawn Grate case resumes on Sept. 25 |url=https://www.richlandsource.com/news/serial-killer-shawn-grate-case-resumes-on-sept/article_4b37d216-bab8-11e8-a225-977fabd6e654.html |accessdate=November 2, 2018 |work=Richland Source |issue=September 24, 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nDefense counsel in the trial were Robert Whitney and Rolf Whitney. The prosecution team was Ashland Prosecutor Chris Tunnell, Medina County Assistant Prosecutor Michael McNamara and Special Prosecutor Mark Weaver.<ref name=\"News Journal Death Sentence\"/>\n\nOn March 1, 2019, Grate pleaded guilty in the murders of Rebekah Leicy and Candice Cunningham, and was sentenced to life in prison without parole for the murder of Leicy, and 17 years to life for the other charges with the sentences running consecutively.<ref>{{cite news|title=Serial killer Grate pleads guilty to killing 2 women in Richland County |url=https://eu.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/2019/03/01/serial-killer-grate-pleads-guilty-2-murders/3019380002/|accessdate=March 1, 2019|work=Mansfield News Journal|date=March 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn September 11, 2019, Grate pleaded guilty in the murder of Dana Lowrey and was sentenced to life in prison without parole plus 16 years.<ref>{{cite news|title=Convicted killer Shawn Grate sentenced to another life term in Marion County death |url=https://www.10tv.com/article/convicted-killer-shawn-grate-sentenced-another-life-term-marion-county-death-2019-sep|accessdate=September 12, 2019|work=10TV|date=September 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Death-row's Grate gets prison term for Marion murder, his first |url=https://eu.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/crime/2019/09/11/serial-killer-shawn-grate-death-row-gets-prison-term-marion-first-murder/2285750001/|accessdate=September 12, 2019|work=Mansfield News Journal|date=September 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Convicted serial killer Shawn Grate pleads guilty to Marion County murder |url=https://www.cleveland19.com/2019/09/11/convicted-serial-killer-shawn-grate-pleads-guilty-marion-county-murder/|accessdate=September 12, 2019|work=Cleveland19|date=September 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Victims ==\n\n===Kidnapping Victim===\nWhile Grate slept, the victim identified by the indictment only as \"Jane Doe\"<ref name=WMFD_69898 /> called 911 from the Ashland house where Grate had held her for three days. She was safely rescued by Ashland police. Because she was the victim of a sexual assault, police declined to reveal her identity.<ref>{{cite web|title=What we know: Shawn Grate tied to 5 deaths, 1 abduction|url=http://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/crime/2016/09/20/shawn-grate-what-we-know/90731792/|website=Cincinnati.com|publisher=USA Today|accessdate=September 20, 2016}}</ref> Grate claims he did not plan to kill her and that they were going to get married.<ref name=QAndACleveland19 />\n\n===Stacey Stanley A.K.A. Stacey Hicks===\nStanley's family had reported her missing the week before Grate was arrested. Her body was found at the Ashland house where Grate was arrested.<ref name=time_9-20-16>{{cite news|last1=Samuelson|first1=Kate|title=Man Linked to at Least 5 Women's Deaths Is 'Obviously a Serial Killer,' Sheriff Says|url=http://time.com/4501103/shawn-grate-murder-kidnapping-obviously-serial-killer/|accessdate=September 20, 2016|work=TIME}}</ref> She is also known as Stacy Hicks. An autopsy concluded she was strangled to death.<ref name=WEWSjan17>{{cite news|last1=Jones|first1=Bob|title=Autopsy report reveals two of Shawn Grate's alleged victims were strangled to death|url=http://www.newsnet5.com/news/local-news/oh-ashland/autopsy-report-reveals-two-of-shawn-grates-alleged-victims-were-strangled-to-death|accessdate=January 4, 2017|work=WEWS|date=January 4, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Elizabeth Griffith===\nGriffith had been missing for about a month before Grate was arrested. Her body was found at the Ashland house where Grate was arrested.<ref name=time_9-20-16 /> An autopsy concluded she was strangled to death.<ref name=WEWSjan17 />\n\n===Candice Cunningham===\nGrate led police to what he claimed was Cunningham's body in neighboring [[Richland County, Ohio|Richland County]] on the day of his arrest.<ref>{{cite news|last1=L'Heureux|first1=Catie|title=A Serial Killer's Victim Made a 911 Call That Helped Police Link the Cases of 5 Murdered Women|url=http://nymag.com/thecut/2016/09/5-women-linked-to-serial-killer-shawn-grate-in-ohio.html|accessdate=September 20, 2016|work=New York Magazine}}</ref> Police found the body behind a house that had previously burned down. The Richland County Sheriff's office officially confirmed that the body found was Cunningham's on November 1, 2016.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Carr|first1=Dillon|title=Candice Cunningham identified as 3rd victim in Grate case|url=http://www.richlandsource.com/news/candice-cunningham-identified-as-rd-victim-in-grate-case/article_608d8396-a042-11e6-86bd-0ff8b86074df.html|accessdate=November 7, 2016|work=Richland Source|date=November 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Rebekah Leicy===\nBased on information supplied by Grate, police have reopened the investigation into Leicy's death. Her body was found in March 2015, and her death was originally ruled a drug overdose.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Whitmire|first1=Lou|title=Grate provides Mansfield police with tips in Leicy case|url=http://www.mansfieldnewsjournal.com/story/news/2016/09/19/mansfield-police-searching-evidence-leicy-investigation/90715336/|accessdate=September 20, 2016|work=Mansfield News Journal}}</ref> Grate says he strangled her after she stole $4 from him in a bar.<ref name=QAndACleveland19 />\n\n===Dana Lowrey===\nGrate claims to have killed another woman who was found dead in [[Marion County, Ohio|Marion County]], Ohio in 2007 who remained unidentified for 12 years.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Barbash|first1=Fred|title='He's obviously a serial killer': Deaths of at least 5 women now linked, probed by Ohio police|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/09/20/hes-obviously-a-serial-killer-deaths-of-at-least-5-women-now-linked-probed-by-ohio-police/|accessdate=September 20, 2016|work=The Washington Post}}</ref> He has stated he believes her name was Dana.<ref name=QAndACleveland19 /> In January 2018, isotope analysis indicated she was likely from the southern United States.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Volpenhein|first1=Sarah|title=New tests could help identify alleged Shawn Grate victim in Marion County|url=https://www.marionstar.com/story/news/crime/2018/04/11/new-leads-naming-first-grate-victim/507374002/|accessdate=April 12, 2018|work=Marion Star|date=April 11, 2018|language=en}}</ref> The victim was identified in June 2019 by the [[DNA Doe Project]] as Dana Nicole Lowrey, 23, of [[Minden, Louisiana]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Marion County Sheriff identifying remains believed to be Shawn Grate's first victim |url=https://myfox28columbus.com/news/local/sheriff-sharing-new-details-on-remains-believed-to-be-shawn-grates-first-victim |accessdate=June 4, 2019 |work=WTTE |date=June 4, 2019}}</ref> Lowrey had two daughters aged one and five  at the time of her death and was separated from her daughters\u2019 father.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/officials-identify-remains-woman-believed-be-shawn-grates-first-victim-2019-jun|title=Officials identify remains of woman believed to be Shawn Grate's first victim|last=Bailey|first=Brittany|date=June 4, 2019|website=WBNS-10TV Columbus, Ohio News, Weather & Sports|language=en|access-date=June 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of serial killers in the United States]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grate, Shawn}}\n\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American serial killers]]\n[[Category:American kidnappers]]\n[[Category:American rapists]]\n[[Category:American criminals]]\n[[Category:American people convicted of murder]]\n[[Category:Male serial killers]]\n[[Category:People convicted of murder by Ohio]]\n[[Category:Prisoners sentenced to death by Ohio]]\n[[Category:Violence against women in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American serial killer on death row}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox criminal\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name = Shawn Grate\n| honorifi