{"title_page": "Alfred Kokot", "text_new": "{{short description|Polish footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Alfred Kokot\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Alfred Kokot\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date |1928|1|25|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Chorz\u00f3w]], Poland\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|1981|6|20|1925|9|10|df=y}} \n| death_place = [[Katowice]], Poland\n| height         = 157cm\n|       position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = Kresy Chorz\u00f3w\n| youthyears2    = 1941\u2013\n| youthclubs2    = Bergknappen Chorz\u00f3w\n| years1         = \u20131945\n| clubs1         = Bergknappen Chorz\u00f3w\n| caps1          = \n| goals1         = \n| years2         = 1945\u20131946\n| clubs2         = Flota Gdynia\n| caps2          = \n| goals2         = \n| years3         = 1946\u20131953\n| clubs3         = [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]]\n| caps3          = 82\n| goals3         = 27\n| years4         = 1953\u20131954\n| clubs4         = G\u00f3rnik 20 Katowice\n| caps4          = \n| goals4         = \n| years5         = 1954\u20131956\n| clubs5         = [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]]\n| caps5          = 27\n| goals5         = 2\n| years6         = 1957\n| clubs6         = [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]]\n| caps6          = \n| goals6         = \n| years7         = 1958\n| clubs7         = [[Mied\u017a Legnica]]\n| caps7          = \n| goals7         = \n| years8         = 1959\u20131961\n| clubs8         = Polonia Tychy\n| caps8          = \n| goals8         = \n| years9         = 1961\u20131963\n| clubs9         = Linodrut Zabrze\n| caps9          = \n| goals9         = \n| totalcaps = \n| totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1       = 1949\n| nationalteam1        = [[Poland national football team|Poland]]\n| nationalcaps1        = 1\n| nationalgoals1       = 1\n}}\n\n'''Alfred Kokot''' (25 January 1928 \u2013 20 June 1981) was a Polish international footballer who played as a forward.\n\n==Biography==\n\nKokot started his career playing with Kresy Chorz\u00f3w and Bergknappen Chorz\u00f3w during his youth years, with the latter being during World War Two. His first professional role came with Flota Gdynia after the war, later joining [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]] in 1946. During his time with Lechia, Kokot made 82 appearances in the leagues, playing 128 times and scoring 51 goals in all competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lechia.net/component/joomleague/player/114-1953-i-liga/1-lechia-gdask/725-alfred-kokot/|title=Alfred Kokot|website=lechia.net}}</ref> During this period he was in the starting eleven which made Lechia's first ever appearance in Poland's top division, a 5\u20131 defeat to [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechiahistoria.pl/2019/03/20/cracovia-lechia-1949/|title=Debiut w ekstraklasie. Cracovia \u2013 Lechia (20.03.1949)|website=lechiahistoria.pl}}</ref> He also made his first, and only appearance for the [[Poland national football team|Poland national team]] with his sole cap coming against Denmark, scoring the goal for Poland in their 2\u20131 defeat,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/freundschaft-1949-juni-polen-daenemark/|title=Poland - Denmark 1:2|website=worldfootball.net}}</ref> becoming Lechia's first player to represent the national team. Kokot left Lechia in 1953, going on to play for G\u00f3rnik 20 Katowice, make 27 league appearances for [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wikigornik.pl/wiki/Alfred_Kokot|title=Alfred Kokot|website=wikigornik.pl}}</ref> [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]], [[Mied\u017a Legnica]], Polonia Tychy, and Linodrut Zabrze. Kokot retired from football aged 38 dying in 1981 at the age of 55.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nHis brother was [[Henryk Kokot]], a footballer who spent his career playing for [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]].\n\nKokot is commemorated by a star at the [[MOSiR Stadium (Gda\u0144sk)|MOSiR Stadium]] in Gda\u0144sk. The \"Avenue of Stars\" commemorates the efforts and success of former players and coaches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gol24.pl/zapomniane-gwiazdy-lechii-gdansk-ze-stadionu-przy-ulicy-traugutta/ar/12261544|title=Zapomniane gwiazdy Lechii Gda\u0144sk ze stadionu przy ulicy Traugutta|website=gol24.pl}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kokot, Alfred}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:1981 deaths]]\n[[Category:Lechia Gda\u0144sk players]]\n[[Category:G\u00f3rnik Zabrze players]]\n[[Category:KS Cracovia players]]\n[[Category:Mied\u017a Legnica players]]\n[[Category:Polish footballers]]\n[[Category:Poland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Polish footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Alfred Kokot\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Alfred Kokot\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date |1925|1|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Chorz\u00f3w]], Poland\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|1981|6|20|1925|9|10|df=y}} \n| death_place = [[Katowice]], Poland\n| height         = 157cm\n|       position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = Kresy Chorz\u00f3w\n| youthyears2    = 1941\u2013\n| youthclubs2    = Bergknappen Chorz\u00f3w\n| years1         = \u20131945\n| clubs1         = Bergknappen Chorz\u00f3w\n| caps1          = \n| goals1         = \n| years2         = 1945\u20131946\n| clubs2         = Flota Gdynia\n| caps2          = \n| goals2         = \n| years3         = 1946\u20131953\n| clubs3         = [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]]\n| caps3          = 82\n| goals3         = 27\n| years4         = 1953\u20131954\n| clubs4         = G\u00f3rnik 20 Katowice\n| caps4          = \n| goals4         = \n| years5         = 1954\u20131956\n| clubs5         = [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]]\n| caps5          = 27\n| goals5         = 2\n| years6         = 1957\n| clubs6         = [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]]\n| caps6          = \n| goals6         = \n| years7         = 1958\n| clubs7         = [[Mied\u017a Legnica]]\n| caps7          = \n| goals7         = \n| years8         = 1959\u20131961\n| clubs8         = Polonia Tychy\n| caps8          = \n| goals8         = \n| years9         = 1961\u20131963\n| clubs9         = Linodrut Zabrze\n| caps9          = \n| goals9         = \n| totalcaps = \n| totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1       = 1949\n| nationalteam1        = [[Poland national football team|Poland]]\n| nationalcaps1        = 1\n| nationalgoals1       = 1\n}}\n\n'''Alfred Kokot''' (28 January 1925 \u2013 20 June 1981) was a Polish international footballer who played as a forward.\n\n==Biography==\n\nKokot started his career playing with Kresy Chorz\u00f3w and Bergknappen Chorz\u00f3w during his youth years, with the latter being during World War Two. His first professional role came with Flota Gdynia after the war, later joining [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]] in 1946. During his time with Lechia, Kokot made 82 appearances in the leagues, playing 128 times and scoring 51 goals in all competitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lechia.net/component/joomleague/player/114-1953-i-liga/1-lechia-gdask/725-alfred-kokot/|title=Alfred Kokot|website=lechia.net}}</ref> During this period he was in the starting eleven which made Lechia's first ever appearance in Poland's top division, a 5\u20131 defeat to [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechiahistoria.pl/2019/03/20/cracovia-lechia-1949/|title=Debiut w ekstraklasie. Cracovia \u2013 Lechia (20.03.1949)|website=lechiahistoria.pl}}</ref> He also made his first, and only appearance for the [[Poland national football team|Poland national team]] with his sole cap coming against Denmark, scoring the goal for Poland in their 2\u20131 defeat,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/freundschaft-1949-juni-polen-daenemark/|title=Poland - Denmark 1:2|website=worldfootball.net}}</ref> becoming Lechia's first player to represent the national team. Kokot left Lechia in 1953, going on to play for G\u00f3rnik 20 Katowice, make 27 league appearances for [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wikigornik.pl/wiki/Alfred_Kokot|title=Alfred Kokot|website=wikigornik.pl}}</ref> [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]], [[Mied\u017a Legnica]], Polonia Tychy, and Linodrut Zabrze. Kokot retired from football aged 38 dying in 1981 at the age of 55.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nHis brother was [[Henryk Kokot]], a footballer who spent his career playing for [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]].\n\nKokot is commemorated by a star at the [[MOSiR Stadium (Gda\u0144sk)|MOSiR Stadium]] in Gda\u0144sk. The \"Avenue of Stars\" commemorates the efforts and success of former players and coaches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gol24.pl/zapomniane-gwiazdy-lechii-gdansk-ze-stadionu-przy-ulicy-traugutta/ar/12261544|title=Zapomniane gwiazdy Lechii Gda\u0144sk ze stadionu przy ulicy Traugutta|website=gol24.pl}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kokot, Alfred}}\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:1981 deaths]]\n[[Category:Lechia Gda\u0144sk players]]\n[[Category:G\u00f3rnik Zabrze players]]\n[[Category:KS Cracovia players]]\n[[Category:Mied\u017a Legnica players]]\n[[Category:Polish footballers]]\n[[Category:Poland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n", "name_user": "S.A. Julio", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix per source", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred_Kokot"}
{"title_page": "List of headphone manufacturers", "text_new": "This is a '''list of headphone manufacturers'''. A [[headphone]] is a pair of small [[loudspeaker]]s that are designed to be held in place close to a user's ears. They are also known as earspeakers, earphones<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web |url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/earphone |title=earphone\n|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref> or, [[colloquially]], cans.<ref>Stanley R. Alten ''Audio Basics'' Cengage 2011 {{ISBN|0-495-91356-1}} page&nbsp;63</ref> The alternative in-ear versions are known as earbuds or earphones.<ref name=\":5\" /> In the context of [[telecommunication]], a [[Headset (audio)|headset]] is a combination of headphone and [[microphone]]. Headphones either have wires for connection to a signal source such as an audio [[amplifier]], [[radio]], [[CD player]], [[portable media player]], [[mobile phone]], [[video game console]]s, [[electronic musical instrument]], or have a [[wireless]] device, which is used to pick up signal without using a cable.\n\n==Headphone manufacturers==\n[[Image:Grado iGrado Street-Style Headphones.jpg|thumb|[[Grado Labs]] iGrado street-style headphones]]\n[[File:Ms Plantro.jpg|thumb|An early [[Plantronics]] [[Headset (audio)|headset]]]]\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n\n*[[AKG (company)|AKG]]\n*[[Allen & Heath]]\n*[[Alesis]]\n*[[Amkette]]\n*[[Andrea Electronics]] \n*[[Arctic (company)|ARCTIC]]\n*[[AudioQuest]]\n*[[Astell&Kern]]\n*[[Asus]]\n*[[Audio-Technica]]\n*[[Bang & Olufsen]]\n*[[Beats Electronics]] \n*[[Behringer]] \n*[[Beyerdynamic]]\n*[https://www.gadgetgroot.com/boat-wireless-headphones/ Boat]\n*[[Boombotix]]\n*[[Bose Corporation]] \n*[[Bowers & Wilkins]]\n*[[Bush (brand)|Bush]]\n*[[Corsair Components]]\n*[[Creative Labs|Creative]] \n*[[Denon]]\n*[[Edifier]] \n*[[Encore Data Products]]\n*[[Fender Musical Instruments Corporation]]\n*[[Fiio]]\n*[[Focal-JMLab|Focal]] \n*[[Focusrite]] \n*[[Fostex]]  \n*[[Goji Electronics]]\n*[[Grado Labs]] \n*[[Harman Kardon]]\n*[[HiFiMAN Electronics]]\n*[[IBall (company)|iBall]] \n*[[iFrogz]]\n*[[Jabra (headset)|Jabra]] \n*[[JBL (company)|JBL]] \n*[[Jerry Harvey (inventor)|JH Audio]] \n*[[JLab Audio]]\n*[[JVC]]\n*[[KEF]] \n*[[Klipsch Audio Technologies]] \n*[[Koss Corporation]] \n*[[Stanton Magnetics|KRK]]\n*[[Kygo Life AS]]\n*[[Logitech]]\n*[[LG]] \n*[[M-Audio]] \n*[[Marshall Amplification]]\n*[[Master & Dynamic]] \n*[[McIntosh Laboratory|McIntosh]] \n*[[Meze Headphones]]\n*[[Monoprice]] \n*[[Monster Cable|Monster]]\n*[[Nakamichi]]\n*[[Onkyo]] \n*[[OPPO Digital]]\n*[[Panasonic]]\n*[[Parrot SA]]\n*[[Philips]]\n*[[Pioneer Corporation|Pioneer]] ([[Pioneer DJ]] line)\n*[[Plantronics Gamecom]]\n*[[PSB Speakers|PSB]]\n*[[Razer Inc.|Razer]]\n*[[RHA Audio]]\n*[[Roland Corporation|Roland]]\n*[[Samsung]]\n*[[Sennheiser]] \n*[[Shure]] \n*[[Skullcandy]]\n*[[SMS Audio]] \n*[[Sol Republic]] \n*[[Sony]] \n*[[Stax Earspeakers]] \n*[[SteelSeries]]\n*[[Technics (brand)|Technics]]\n*[[Thinksound]] \n*[[Turtle Beach Systems]]  \n*[[Ultimate Ears]]\n*[[Ultrasone]] \n*[[Urbanears]] \n*[[V-MODA]]\n*[[Velodyne]]\n*[[Vox (musical equipment)]]\n*[[Westone]]\n*[[Yamaha]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Companies|Electronics}}\n\n* [[Consumer electronics]]\n* [[List of microphone manufacturers]]\n* [[List of loudspeaker manufacturers]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Headphones manufacturers| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of consumer electronics manufacturers|Headphone manufacturers]]\n[https://www.gadgetgroot.com/boat-wireless-headphones/ Boat wireless headphones]\n", "text_old": "This is a '''list of headphone manufacturers'''. A [[headphone]] is a pair of small [[loudspeaker]]s that are designed to be held in place close to a user's ears. They are also known as earspeakers, earphones<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web |url=http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/earphone |title=earphone\n|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref> or, [[colloquially]], cans.<ref>Stanley R. Alten ''Audio Basics'' Cengage 2011 {{ISBN|0-495-91356-1}} page&nbsp;63</ref> The alternative in-ear versions are known as earbuds or earphones.<ref name=\":5\" /> In the context of [[telecommunication]], a [[Headset (audio)|headset]] is a combination of headphone and [[microphone]]. Headphones either have wires for connection to a signal source such as an audio [[amplifier]], [[radio]], [[CD player]], [[portable media player]], [[mobile phone]], [[video game console]]s, [[electronic musical instrument]], or have a [[wireless]] device, which is used to pick up signal without using a cable.\n\n==Headphone manufacturers==\n[[Image:Grado iGrado Street-Style Headphones.jpg|thumb|[[Grado Labs]] iGrado street-style headphones]]\n[[File:Ms Plantro.jpg|thumb|An early [[Plantronics]] [[Headset (audio)|headset]]]]\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n\n*[[AKG (company)|AKG]]\n*[[Allen & Heath]]\n*[[Alesis]]\n*[[Amkette]]\n*[[Andrea Electronics]] \n*[[Arctic (company)|ARCTIC]]\n*[[AudioQuest]]\n*[[Astell&Kern]]\n*[[Asus]]\n*[[Audio-Technica]]\n*[[Bang & Olufsen]]\n*[[Beats Electronics]] \n*[[Behringer]] \n*[[Beyerdynamic]]\n*[[Boombotix]]\n*[[Bose Corporation]] \n*[[Bowers & Wilkins]]\n*[[Bush (brand)|Bush]]\n*[[Corsair Components]]\n*[[Creative Labs|Creative]] \n*[[Denon]]\n*[[Edifier]] \n*[[Encore Data Products]]\n*[[Fender Musical Instruments Corporation]]\n*[[Fiio]]\n*[[Focal-JMLab|Focal]] \n*[[Focusrite]] \n*[[Fostex]]  \n*[[Goji Electronics]]\n*[[Grado Labs]] \n*[[Harman Kardon]]\n*[[HiFiMAN Electronics]]\n*[[IBall (company)|iBall]] \n*[[iFrogz]]\n*[[Jabra (headset)|Jabra]] \n*[[JBL (company)|JBL]] \n*[[Jerry Harvey (inventor)|JH Audio]] \n*[[JLab Audio]]\n*[[JVC]]\n*[[KEF]] \n*[[Klipsch Audio Technologies]] \n*[[Koss Corporation]] \n*[[Stanton Magnetics|KRK]]\n*[[Kygo Life AS]]\n*[[Logitech]]\n*[[LG]] \n*[[M-Audio]] \n*[[Marshall Amplification]]\n*[[Master & Dynamic]] \n*[[McIntosh Laboratory|McIntosh]] \n*[[Meze Headphones]]\n*[[Monoprice]] \n*[[Monster Cable|Monster]]\n*[[Nakamichi]]\n*[[Onkyo]] \n*[[OPPO Digi